OL,6,FHe said Lloyd-Hall had carried a knife
OL,7,Fto feel "powerful" and out of
OL,8,F"bravado" ` and not for protection, as
OL,9,Fhe had claimed in his trial.
OL,11,FThe judge told him: "You stabbed Harry
OL,12,Fbecause you lost your temper with him
OL,13,Fand you acted like a big man in front
OL,14,Fof your friends."
OL,16,FIn that "split second", he must have
OL,17,Frealised Harry might be killed or
OL,18,Finjured, but Mr Justice Cavanagh said:
OL,19,F"In the moment, you did not care if he
OL,20,Flived or died."
