OL,6,F'If you had not taken a knife to
OL,7,FPrimerose Hill that night, Harry
OL,8,FPitman would still be alive'
OL,10,FThe judge told the defendant: "If you
OL,11,Fhad not taken a knife to Primrose Hill
OL,12,Fthat night, Harry Pitman would still
OL,13,Fbe alive, he would have his whole life
OL,14,Fahead of him, and his family and
OL,15,Ffriends would not have been plunged
OL,16,Finto the most profound and awful grief.
OL,18,F"What turned it into a terrible and
OL,19,Ftragic incident was your decision, for
OL,20,Fno good reason whatsoever, to arm
OL,21,Fyourself with a knife.
